11	South Wales & Celtic Manor	south-wales-celtic-manor	# South Wales & Celtic Manor\r\n\r\nSouthern Wales is home to some of the UK’s most spectacular coastlines which has lent itself to the creation of some of the most stunning links courses in Europe. Not only is the South coast of Wales home to such an array of breathtaking links courses, it is also home to Celtic Manor which shot to the forefront of golf when it hosted the 2010 Ryder Cup matches. \r\n\r\nThis impressive array of golfing options is backed up by outstanding accommodation, wonderful beaches that are perfect for surfing and of course the local towns and villages where a warm welcome awaits. \r\n\r\nFamous names in Welsh golf including Royal Porthcawl and the James Braid designed Pennard Links may end up being the highlights of this tour but they will face stiff competition from some of the country’s lesser known hidden gems. Pyle & Kenfig may not draw the same plaudits as its more illustrious neighbours but it is a truly magical links course that will set the heart racing if the wind gets up. Machynys Peninsula is home to the first Jack Nicklaus designed golf course in Wales and while it looks out over Carmarthen Bay it is by no means a traditional links course and as such will provide some glorious variety to the golf tour.\r\n\r\nMoving on from the Dragon Hotel in Swansea golfers will head to Celtic Manor for the remainder of the tour where they will be treated to the picturesque Roman Road Course, five star accommodation, amazing restaurants and of course the Twenty Ten Course. The Twenty Ten Course was the first golf course to be purpose built for the Ryder Cup and a round here is a truly special and atmospheric experience; perfect for wrapping up a golf tour of South Wales.	2011-08-30 16:19:21.794488	2011-09-13 14:36:39.794344	tours	51.677665,-2.809753	9	Wales	South Wales & Celtic Manor Golf Tours | Your Golf Tours	\N
