20	Royal Troon	royal-troon	#Royal Troon\r\n\r\nFounded in 1878 by a few enthusiasts Troon Golf Club soon outgrew its purely local reputation.\r\n\r\nThe Old Course today presents a stern golfing examination and in particular the inward half of Royal Troon is widely accepted as the most demanding of any Course on the Championship rota.\r\n\r\nOne of the great links courses in Scotland, the Old Course is a challenging test of golfing ability. With the wind to contend with, and deep rough interspersed with gorse and broom, accurate shot making is essential. Players should make their scores on the outward nine, as the prevailing north-westerly wind can make the back nine extremely difficult.\r\n\r\nCharles Hunter, "Keeper of the Green" at Prestwick Golf Club, supervised the clearance of the ground and the laying out of the first five-hole Course. A sixth hole was added during 1879, with further extensions firstly to twelve holes and then to eighteen, which was completed in 1885. The development to twelve and then to eighteen holes was agreed by a group of enthusiasts along with George Strath the Club’s Professional. Further changes were undertaken on the recommendations of Willie Fernie, Strath’s successor. Prior to the 1923 Open Championship alterations were made on the advice of James Braid.\r\n\r\nIn men’s golf, the Club has hosted the Amateur Championship on four occasions, the Scottish Amateur Championship on five occasions, the Scottish Open Amateur Stroke-play Championship on one occasion and the Men’s Home International Championships on four occasions.\r\n\r\nIn ladies’ golf, the Ladies British Open Amateur Championship has been played at Troon on four occasions and the Scottish Ladies Close Amateur Championship on five occasions.\r\n\r\nThe Club is situated on the West Coast of Scotland 35 miles south of Glasgow and close to the County Town of Ayr. Panoramic Views of the Firth of Clyde, looking out to the Isle of Arran and Ailsa Craig, (Paddy’s Milestone) will immediately delight and enthral the first time visitor. Prestwick Golf Club and Turnberry Golf Club are both within easy driving distance of Royal Troon, each having a history of Open Championship golf participation.	2011-08-31 14:03:28.597774	2011-09-13 10:38:44.121333	courses		\N	Scotland	Royal Troon Golf Tours | Your Golf Tours	One of the great links courses in Scotland, the Old Course is a challenging test of golfing ability. With the wind to contend with, and deep rough interspersed with gorse and broom, accurate shot making is essential.
186	The Celtic Manor Resort	the-celtic-manor-resort	#The Celtic Manor Resort\r\n\r\nWales' flagship golf destination is The Celtic Manor Resort, a unique complex that has not only transformed the country's golfing landscape, but also attracted The 2010 Ryder Cup. Highlights of the splendid retreat include three terrific championship courses, two hotels - one 4* and one 5* - a phenomenal spa and outstanding dining.\r\n\r\nWe recommend the Resort Hotel, which is the five-star offering at The Celtic Manor, as it provides the most luxurious accommodation and immediate access to facilities and restaurants. Enjoy the Merlins Bar, located in the hotel's main foyer, and the ultimate service and dining of the Crown Restaurant, the resort's top rated kitchen.\r\n\r\nIn the Forum Health Club and Spa, golfers or their non-playing companions will enjoy one of the UK's premier relaxation retreats. Whether it is a swim in the amazing pool or indulging with a specifically tailored treatment, the Forum is a highlight of any stay at the resort.\r\n\r\nThe Lodge at The Celtic Manor serves as the resort's golf clubhouse; it is centrally located, providing easy access to the first tees of both the Montgomerie and Roman Road courses. The Twenty Ten Course, host of The Ryder Cup, has its own luxury clubhouse, and is accessed by transfer from the hotel.\r\n\r\nEvery one of the 330 guest rooms and suites in the Resort Hotel ensures a splendid base for your Celtic Manor experience; contemporary in style and fitted with five-star amenities, the Resort is the appropriate complement for The Celtic Manor's iconic Ryder Cup golf course.	2011-09-02 15:51:36.80136	2011-09-08 16:02:55.927824	hotels		\N	Wales	The Celtic Manor Resort, Wales | Your Golf Tours	Every one of the 330 guest rooms and suites in the Resort Hotel ensures a splendid base for your Celtic Manor experience; contemporary in style and fitted with five-star amenities, the Resort is the appropriate complement for The Celtic Manor's iconic Ryder Cup golf course.
22	Kingsbarns	kingsbarns	#Kingsbarns\r\n\r\nThere are several courses in the St Andrews area and Kingsbarns, which is located just outside the town, is a must play.\r\n\r\nGolf was played there for many years in the 1800’s but it was the 1990’s when Kingsbarns benefited from a massive redevelopment and is now regarded as one of Scotland’s best courses.\r\n\r\nThe Kingsbarns Golf Links site has long been known for its intimate connection with the sea. The fact that it`s golf origins date back to 1793 is testimony to the attributes of the site which foster ideal conditions for links turf to flourish amid interesting natural terrain.\r\n\r\nThis unique part of East Fife has sandy soils, undulating ridges and hollows, Cambo burn running into the sea, all set immediately against the rugged coastline of the North Sea.\r\n\r\nKingsbarns has marked the name of Kyle Phillips on the golfing map with a bang, as praise has been gushing for the dramatic coastal layout; the humps, hollows and dunes that have been carefully scuplted combine to form outstanding holes like the 12th, a striking par-5 that wraps its way along the shores with the beach in easy reach, and also the 15th, a phenomenal short hole across the water.\r\n\r\nThe non-membership model means that Kingsbarns has an open, welcoming atmosphere, with a small but extremely comfortable clubhouse that overlooks the treacherous final green. The golf course is within a few minutes of St Andrews and the Fairmont Resort, making it accessible - this is arguably the best course to be opened in the UK in decades, so be sure you don't miss out. Kingsbarns is open from April through October.	2011-08-31 14:04:48.23664	2011-09-08 15:35:12.239315	courses		\N	Scotland	Golf at Kingsbarns, St Andrews, Scotland | Your Golf Tours	The Kingsbarns Golf Links site has long been known for its intimate connection with the sea. The fact that it`s golf origins date back to 1793 is testimony to the attributes of the site which foster ideal conditions for links turf to flourish amid interesting natural terrain.
