80	Sunningdale	sunningdale	#Sunningdale\r\n\r\nFew inland golf courses in England are as highly regarded as Sunningdale, a revered name in the game and the owner of two sublime layouts. Winding through the woodland of Surrey to the south of London and fringed by stunning heather, Sunningdale must be played to be truly appreciated.\r\n\r\nThe Old Course at Sunningdale was unveiled in 1901, and designed by Willie Park Jnr., a man inextricably linked with the development of golf in the British Isles at the turn of the century. As it winds through the woodland and heather, the Old serves up a glorious variation of holes that together make up one of England's very best courses.\r\n\r\nIn 1923, Sunningdale added the New Course to the existing Old, courtesy of a design by Harry S. Colt, whose fingerprints are all over the best heathland courses in Surrey and Berkshire. The New is distinctly different in style, more rugged and certainly a stern test, and it represents the ideal complement to its neighbour. Whichever you choose, Sunningdale will be tough to beat in terms of highlights from you golf tour around London.	2011-08-31 15:54:05.719504	2011-09-08 15:52:26.176804	courses		\N	Scotland	Golf at Sunningdale, Surrey, England | Your Golf Tours	Few inland golf courses in England are as highly regarded as Sunningdale, a revered name in the game and the owner of two sublime layouts. Winding through the woodland of Surrey to the south of London and fringed by stunning heather, Sunningdale must be played to be truly appreciated.
