138	Gleneagles	gleneagles	#Gleneagles\r\n\r\nWhen we talk about Gleneagles golf we are mainly making reference to the 3 Championship courses at The Gleneagles Hotel, The Kings, Queens and the PGA Centenary course which is set to host the 2014 Ryder Cup matches.\r\n\r\nThe 5 star hotel is world renowned with a plethora of facilities and services to choose from. The golf speaks for itself; 54 holes of exquisite golf with each course as good as the other 2. More recent developments in the hotel mean that The Gleneagles Hotel now has one of the best equipped Spas in the country.\r\n\r\nThe countryside around Gleneagles is absolutely stunning and of course, you won't have to travel far to visit a local distillery. For golf in Scotland Gleneagles ideally located, within 1 hour of Glasgow, Edinburgh and St Andrews making it a perfect place to set up base for an extended period.	2011-09-01 16:45:48.720883	2011-09-06 15:40:46.067942	regions		\N	Scotland	Golf in Gleneagles | Your Golf Tours	\N
136	Highlands, Dornoch & Nairn	highlands-dornoch-nairn	#Highlands, Dornoch & Nairn\r\n\r\nRoyal Dornoch Golf Club is the main course in the Scottish Highlands. In 1981 Tom Watson, after winning the third of 5 Opens, travelled to Royal Dornoch to play 18 holes; he ended up playing 3 rounds and said that it was "the most fun I've ever had on a golf course". He is now an honorary member of the club.\r\n\r\nThe first three golf links golf courses in Scotland of which there is written record are: 1552, St Andrews; 1593, Leith; 1616, Dornoch. It was in 1877 that the Dornoch Golf Club was founded as the successor of the Sutherland Golfing Society whose members played at Dornoch and Golspie. The superb Carnegie Shield was presented to the club by Mr and Mrs. Andrew Carnegie in 1901 for annual competition, and the link with the United States was forged more closely when they opened a new clubhouse in 1909.\r\n\r\nOther Local golf courses include Lossiemouth, Golspie, Brora, Boat of Garten, Tain and Nairn. For quality Scottish golf courses one need look no further than the area surrounding Dornoch which is magical. The drive from Glasgow or Edinburgh is about 4 hours, but one can stop after about 3 hours to play the new Spey Valley golf course, designed by Dave Thomas.\r\n\r\nThe Royal Dornoch Golf Hotel is located on the first hole of the championship course at Dornoch and has recently been refurbished to offer superior accommodation.\r\n\r\nInverness, being the capital of the Highlands, has become an attractive place to stay in recent years with travelling time to all the courses in the area under an hour.\r\n\r\nThe completion in 2009 of the glorious championship course at Castle Stuart has transformed the face of golf in the Scottish Highlands; the layout is a true international star, and ranks up there with any links course in Scotland. Book up your itinerary now and experience it for yourself.	2011-09-01 16:45:02.771914	2011-09-06 15:41:47.604981	regions		\N	Scotland	Golf in The Highlands, Dornoch, Nairn, Castle Stuart | Your Golf Tours	\N
141	Southport	southport	#Southport\r\n\r\nSouthport lies at the heart of what is informally called 'England's Golf Coast', referring to the fact that this corner of North West England and its Lancashire shoreline is absolutely packed with golf of the highest order. These include household names, British Open venues and some hidden gems that await your discovery.\r\n\r\nYour golf tour in England can be a chance to tackle the region's three Open Championship golf courses; within easy reach of Southport, which we recommend as a base, are the Royal trio of Birkdale, Lytham and Liverpool. All three are top quality layouts and prestigious clubs, but access for visitors is generally excellent.\r\n\r\nBack these up by exploring the likes of Southport & Ainsdale and Hillside, which may not carry the Royal adornment but are superb links courses. The huge bonus of the area is that all the courses are packed into an extremely small radius, cutting down driving time.\r\n\r\nSouthport itself is a traditional English seaside resort town, and its focal point, Lord Street, has plenty of bars and restaurants. Access to Southport is easy from the airports at Liverpool and Manchester.	2011-09-01 16:47:24.035957	2011-09-07 16:34:07.966282	regions		\N	England	British Open Golf venues – Birkdale, Royal Liverpool| Your Golf Tours	\N
