60	Longniddry Golf Club	longniddry-golf-club	#Longniddry Golf Club\r\n\r\nLongniddry Golf Course is a unique combination of parkland and links located on the south side of Firth of Forth.\r\n\r\nThere are no (men’s) par 5’s although some of the par 4`s are very testing, particularly into the prevailing westerly winds; this is reflected by the SSS of 70 – 2 shots above the par of 68.\r\n\r\nThe course is not long by modern standards, but it is designed to reward the strategic player. The fairways are quite generous and the greens are fairly large, but the penalty for straying off-line can be severe. You will find mature Scots Pines, gorse, sea-buckthorn and punitive rough only too eager to punish the wayward drive. Hit it long, certainly, but you’d better be straight!\r\n\r\nThe opening holes are relatively straightforward and open to the winds of the estuary. From the 3rd green to the 11th tee there is considerable shelter in amongst the trees, but thereafter the course opens out once more.\r\n\r\nThere are many good holes at Longniddry, both as a test of golf and of natural beauty. They include the 450 yard 3rd, which is right on the limit for a par 4; the 305 yard dogleg 5th, with a two-tier elevated green; the 6th, with a shot of 160 yards downhill to the heavily bunkered green and the long 7th. The closing six holes are equally challenging, particularly the dogleg 12th, the par 3 13th and the finishing hole of 418 yards, where par is always welcome.\r\n\r\nThe Club is a former venue of the British Seniors and a qualifier for the Open at Muirfield. More recently the Club has hosted the Ladies Home Internationals and the Commonwealth Youths Tournament. It is a regional qualifier for the Lombard PGA ProAm and a number of other competitions.\r\n\r\nThis area of East Lothian area enjoys a relatively dry climate, with an average long-term rainfall of 14". The course is very free draining and rarely suffers from the indignity of closure, even during the winter. The greens in recent years have been fast and true, and the course itself is invariably in excellent condition. 	2011-08-31 15:15:45.646958	2011-09-08 15:38:08.376439	courses		\N	Scotland	Golf at Longniddry Golf Club, East Lothian, Scotland | Your Golf Tours	Longniddry Golf Course is a unique combination of parkland and links located on the south side of Firth of Forth.
16	The Algarve	the-algarve	# The Algarve\r\n\r\nThe Algarve is replete with top class golf courses, hotels and resorts that have earned Portugal its reputation as the premier golf holiday destination in Europe. Synonymous with golf, the Algarve benefits from a pleasant year round climate that is simply perfect for playing golf under the sun.\r\n\r\nDona Filipa is one of the very best golf resorts in Europe and is the first port of call on this golf tour. Not only does Donna Filipa offer five star accommodation, outstanding facilities and best of all exclusive access to the San Lorenzo golf course which is widely regarded to be the very best in the whole of Portugal. As well as San Lorenzo golfers will also pay other Algarve heavyweights a visit including the Oceanico Victoria and Old Courses and the Royal Course at Vale do Lobo which boasts one of the most famous holes in the world.   \r\n\r\nOnce your time at Dona Filipa is up fear not; as you will be heading for yet more five star luxury and outstanding golf courses. Nestled in 2000 acres of rolling hills and majestic pine forests, Quinta do Lago offers golfers truly luxurious surroundings and world class golf is never too far away. \r\n\r\nThe golfing delights that make up the remainder of the Algarve Tour include the Jack Nicklaus designed Monte Rei and the picturesque Quinta do Lago South Course which is one of the most illustrious courses in the country having hosted countless professional events including the Portuguese Open on an impressive eight occasions.	2011-08-30 16:27:11.240477	2011-09-13 10:07:06.564588	tours	37.1636,-7.499542	10	Portugal	Algarve Golf Tours - San Lorenzo, Quinta Do Lago, | Your Golf Tours	\N
