90	Carton House	carton-house	#Carton House\r\n\r\nMultiple host to the European Tour's Irish Open, Carton House is a top quality golfing complex with two splendid courses at its heart. No expense was spared in crafting an unrivalled experience, and Carton House's developers drafted in two of the game's heavy hitters to lay out the courses - Colin Montgomerie and American Mark O'Meara.\r\n\r\nThe Montgomerie Course was the host of the 2005 and 2006 Nissan Irish Opens, and is a monumental championship test; expansive bunkering and the wild grasses of the Emerald Isle set the stage for a tremendous layout. Monty, Europe's Ryder Cup Captain for 2010, drew influence from his favourite courses worldwide, which include Royal Melbourne and Turnberry, in creating what has developed into one of Ireland's premier courses.\r\n\r\nOn the banks of the River Wye is Carton House's other course, the O'Meara. Choose Mark's layout if you feel like a slightly more sedate challenge; less fearsome than the Montgomerie, the O'Meara is an equally enjoyable part of any good Irish golf tour.	2011-08-31 16:02:00.760185	2011-09-13 16:56:42.294067	courses	53.517451,-5.394287	9	Ireland	Golf at Carton House, Ireland | Your Golf Tours	Multiple host to the European Tour's Irish Open, Carton House is a top quality golfing complex with two splendid courses at its heart. No expense was spared in crafting an unrivalled experience, and Carton House's developers drafted in two of the game's heavy hitters to lay out the courses - Colin Montgomerie and American Mark O'Meara.
