134	Aberdeen & Cruden Bay	aberdeen-cruden-bay	#Aberdeen & Cruden Bay\r\n\r\nAberdeen is the capital of Scotland’s North East Coast, known internationally as the granite city due to the extensive use of this local stone in the city's architecture.\r\n\r\nAmong our recommended hotels to begin your golf tour around Aberdeen is the luxury Inchmarlo Resort. Located on the beautiful Royal Deeside, the complex has spectacular natural surroundings, while on the resort is a collection of superb accommodation units, a fine dining restaurant and two lovely golf courses.\r\n\r\nThe Udny Arms is a popular and relaxed accommodation option for golfing visitors to Aberdeen; the laid back atmosphere is the ideal preparation for exploring the likes of Royal Aberdeen and Crudern Bay, two stars of the golfing landscape around the city. We recommend for multi-stop golf tours in Scotland that Aberdeen is easily twinned with either the Highlands and Royal Dornoch, or St Andrews down the coast to the South.\r\n\r\nCruden Bay Golf Club is only 40 minutes North of Aberdeen and the view from the clubhouse gives you a flavour of the dramatic dunes and landscape you will encounter on your way round this rugged links.\r\n\r\nThe Marcliffe is only a few minutes away from the Balgownie Links at Royal Aberdeen Golf Club and is a golfer friendly hotel that will complement your golf tour in Scotland.	2011-09-01 16:44:16.574643	2011-09-07 11:01:54.022755	regions		\N	Scotland	Highlands & Royal Aberdeen Golf – Castle Stuart | Your Golf Tours	\N
137	Edinburgh & East Lothian	edinburgh-east-lothian	#Edinburgh & East Lothian\r\n\r\nEdinburgh, or "Auld Reekie" as it is lovingly called by the locals, makes reference to the numerous industries that used to spew plumes of smoke into the city sky. A visit to the Castle has to be included in any trip to Edinburgh. If visiting during the month of August one can experience the Military Tattoo which runs for 3 weeks on the Castle's Esplanade.\r\n\r\nThe Royal Mile is the main tourist area of Edinburgh and stretches from Edinburgh Castle to Hollyrood Palace (the Queen's official Edinburgh residence), where there are many shops and restaurants to sample and also the chance to tour the underground vaults of the Old Town.\r\n\r\nGolf in the area ranges from Dalmahoy in the East across to a fantastic stretch of Scottish links courses including 3 courses at Gullane, North Berwick West Links, Muirfield, Dunbar, Craigielaw and Longniddry.\r\n\r\nThe drive from Edinburgh to Dunbar (the furthest course down the coast) is only about 40 minutes, making a stay in the city centre a very plausible option. However, we have a selection of hotels closer to all the courses including the Marriott Dalmahoy Resort and Marine North Berwick which overlooks the West Links of North Berwick.\r\n\r\nOne of the best selections of golf courses in Scotland is to be found in this area, local Scottish golf has never been better.	2011-09-01 16:45:23.340168	2011-09-06 15:40:35.325526	regions		\N	Scotland	Golf in Edinburgh & East Lothian | Your Golf Tours	\N
