139	St Andrews	st-andrews	#St Andrews\r\n\r\nGolf in Scotland is not complete without a pilgrimage to St Andrews – the Home of Golf, and although obtaining a tee time over the Old Course is challenging in some months, we can guarantee packages to include a coveted reservation. But remember that Scotland has another 5 Open Championship venues past and present, which offer Links golf at its best.\r\n\r\nIn and around St Andrews the keen golfer could play a round on a different course each day and play for 2 weeks without travelling more than 30 minutes to reach a course.\r\n\r\nThe town of St Andrews is one of the largest small towns in Scotland. The university, where Prince William attended, attracts students from all over the world, keeping the bars and restaurants busy during the winter, and during the summer golfers from all over the world descend on the town to play the hallowed Old Course. The town has got a mystical charm about it!\r\n\r\nSt Andrews was home to Old Tom Morris and his son, funnily enough called Young Tom Morris, the youngest ever winner of the Open championship at the age of 17 and won it 4 times in a row. Old and Young Tom Morris dominated the Open's and they won it 8 times between them from 1860-72. However the story of Young Tom Morris is ultimately a tragic one. His wife of one year was taken ill during childbirth and a telegram was dispatched to call Morris to her bedside. It was given to him as he came off the course at North Berwick. While in transit home, another telegram arrived with the grim news that she died. Morris never recovered from the shock. He died of a broken heart some same, a few months later on Christmas Day 1875 at the tender age of 24.\r\n\r\nA memorial was erected at his grave on which was inscribed "Deeply regretted by numerous friends and all golfers, he thrice in succession won the Championship Belt and held it without envy, his many amiable qualities being no less acknowledged than his golfing achievements". His grave is located in the ruined cathedral of St Andrews.\r\n\r\nOld Tom Morris passed away in 1908 at the age of 86.	2011-09-01 16:46:18.728013	2011-09-06 15:46:25.894646	regions		\N	Scotland	Golf in St Andrews, Old Course, Kingsbarns, -  Your Golf Tours	\N
